  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Fretheim Hotel in Flam is situated in a beautiful location with great access to other areas on the Sognefjord.</p>
<h2>One of Flam’s original hotels</h2>
<p>The Fretheim Hotel has an interesting history in Flam. Back in the 1800s, wealthy travellers from overseas would venture to the Sognefjord to take part in salmon fishing and would often seek accommodation in Flam. They would stay at Christen Fretheim’s farm and to meet demand, the farmer ended up opening a hotel on the site. Today, you’ll see a historic building with modern elements that have been added over the years but it still remains a fantastic base for exploring the Sognefjord.</p>
<h2>A great stopping point to explore the Sognefjord</h2>
<p>Flam is a popular destination for many visitors to Norway and it’s not hard to see why. Sitting on one of the branches of the Sognefjord you’re in reaching distance of those beautiful vistas. The Flam Railway is also a must-do for this area (its best to book and pay in advance). Skirt through the valley and keep an eye out for waterfalls and dramatic landscapes. It’s also a good area to base yourself to connect to other local towns or, take part in a day trip that heads into the Fjords.</p>
<p><strong>This hotel is only bookable as part of a multi-centre, please call to book.</strong></p>]]></description>
